The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, July 12 (PTI): The Supreme Court has ruled that even if a landlord refuses to accept the rent the tenant has to compulsorily deposit it with the rent controller (court), failing which the tenant could be evicted.          
	The ruling was passed upholding an appeal filed by a landlord in a dispute with the tenant.                   
	 Lucknow (PTI): Three policemen have been arrested on the charges of dereliction of duty and helping an undertrial escape while being brought to Lucknow jail. Head constable Asharam Sudhakar and constables Ramayan Yadav and Shyamji Mishra have been suspended and arrested.                  
	 Islamabad (PTI): An Indian died of a heart attack while travelling on the Thar Express in Pakistans Sindh province. The 50-year-old man, identified as Shagan, a resident of Ahmedabad, died on Saturday at a railway station, officials said. His body has been handed over to Indian authorities.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): A first womens battalion of about 1,000 personnel will be inducted in the BSF for combat duties by the end of this month. The women, who are currently training at the BSF establishment in Khatka, Punjab, will participate in the passing out parade on July 29, to be attended by Union home minister P. Chidambaram.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): Delhi High Court has directed the directorate-general of civil aviation to give its views on the requirement for pilots to give a six-month notice to an airline before leaving. The directive came after Jet Airways filed a petition challenging the order of a single-member bench that had in May 2009 allowed a pilot to leave the company.                                                                                                                           
